  <div id="preteen-er"></div>
  <HorizontalCard
    title="Naturalistic Emotion Regulation in Preteens During Peer Interactions"
    img="/preteen_ER.png"
    desc="I am leading in the development of novel protocol for a pilot grant in studying encoding of social and emotional cues and emotion regulation in pre-teens during peer interactions capitalizing on less-motion sensitive DOT neuroimaging. Unlike passive viewing, real-life interactions require bidirectional regulation: teens must manage their own emotions while also considering how their expressions influence their peer's emotional state. This paradigm could reveal how the brain coordinates multiple regulatory systems to navigate the complex demands of social emotion regulation. I hypothesize children with maladaptive emotion regulation skills would have less neural discrimination of different emotions and heightened sensitivity to irrelevant stimuli."
